OL,3,CUniversity fined #585,000 following
OL,4,Cfree speech investigation
OL,6,F"So it is right that we investigate
OL,7,Fwhere we have concerns that students
OL,8,Fmay not be benefiting from the free
OL,9,Fand robust exchange of ideas, or that
OL,10,Facademics are not able to teach or
OL,11,Fresearch what they choose."
OL,13,FHe said the university had made
OL,14,F"significant and serious breaches" of
OL,15,Fthe OfS's requirements and the
OL,16,Fpenalties were "appropriate for the
OL,17,Fscale of wrongdoing we found".
OL,19,FProfessor Roseneil warned of the
OL,20,Fimplications of the report's outcome
OL,21,Ffor the wider higher education sector.
